      • getImpl

        public String getImpl()
        The direct classpath lookup name for a particular check. If not provided, indicates that a check should be looked up by name from a catalog on the classpath.
        Returns:
        className or script resource name of a ProgressCheck or ProgressCheckFactory.

      • setImpl

        public void setImpl(String impl)

      • getName

        public String getName()
        The display name for the check. If "impl" is provided, and represents a script package check or a class that implements ProgressCheckFactory this is treated as an alias for the check during this execution.

        If "impl" is not provided, this is used to lookup a catalog check.

        If "impl" is not a ProgressCheckFactory, this value is ignored.

        Returns:
        the checkName
